            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Review quarterly. Google adds new categories throughout the year, and competitor changes in the Map Pack can signal a better primary choice. Switching primary categories may cause 1–2 weeks of temporary ranking fluctuation.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Do secondary categories help with ranking?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes, but significantly less than the primary category. Secondaries expand the set of searches you can appear for. They do not carry the ranking weight the primary does.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How do I pick the right primary GBP category?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Pick the most specific option that accurately describes your core service. Then check what categories the top 3 competitors in the Map Pack use — if their primary category matches, you should probably match too.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>

